<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-624-892  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 624 892.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  June 25 1990 v4 n25 p23(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fiber optics: on the horizon.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>King, Julia.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>High cost and lack of experienced maintenance technicians isslowing widespread federal implementation of fiber-optic networks,but some agencies have installed them.andP;  The increasing power,capacity and data transfer demands of federal computing activitieswill expand the use of high-bandwidth fiber-optic communicationstechnologies.andP;  The FBI is already sending all of its voice trafficover the FTS 2000 Network B fiber-optic voice network and leasingcommercial fiber-optic circuits for 'much of its long-haul datatraffic' between headquarters and field offices.andP;  NASA LangleyResearch Center (Hampton, VA) has a Fiber-Distributed DataInterface fiber-optic network linking Ethernet local area networks(LANs) in two buildings.andP;  Maguire Air Force Base (NJ) selected afiber-optic 10Net secure LAN for a mobile airlift control centerbecause it offered security, speed and high capacity.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Optical CommunicationsFiber OpticsWide Area NetworksLocal Area NetworksNational GovernmentGovernment AgencyImplementationApplicationsUnited States. Federal Bureau of InvestigationUnited States. Langley Research CenterUnited States. Air Force.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>